The '''Dodge 330''' was a [[Full-size car|full-size]] automobile sold by [[Dodge]] from 1962 to and 1964, and was based on the [[Chrysler B platform|B-body]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Standard Catalog of American Cars 1946-1975|publisher=krause publications|isbn=0-87341-027-0|editor=Gunnell, John A.}}</ref> The [[coupe]] often used a 6-cylinder engine.  The car was available as a 2dr Sedan or 4dr Sedan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldcarbrochures.com/static/NA/Dodge/1963_Dodge/1963_Dodge_Standard_Size_Brochure/1963%20Dodge%20Standard%20Size-09.html |title=Directory Index: Dodge/1963_Dodge/1963_Dodge_Standard_Size_Brochure |publisher=Oldcarbrochures.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-20}}</ref>  Base motor was the [[Chrysler Slant-6 engine|225 Slant-Six]].  The [[Chrysler A engine|318 2bbl]], [[Chrysler B engine|361 2bbl, 383 2bbl, 383 4bbl]], and [[Chrysler RB engine|426 4bbl]] were optional. As an intermediate trim level above the Dart, it came standard with a cigarette lighter, front foam cushions, and rear arm rests.<ref>{{cite book|title=Standard Catalog of American Cars 1946-1975|publisher=krause publications|isbn=0-87341-027-0|editor=Gunnell, John A.}}</ref> The car had a {{convert|119|in|mm|abbr=on}} wheelbase and was {{convert|208.1|in|mm|abbr=on}} long.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oldcarbrochures.com/static/NA/Dodge/1963_Dodge/1963_Dodge_Standard_Size_Brochure/1963%20Dodge%20Standard%20Size-13.html |title=Directory Index: Dodge/1963_Dodge/1963_Dodge_Standard_Size_Brochure |publisher=Oldcarbrochures.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-20}}</ref> There was also a higher trimmed [[Dodge 440|440]] and [[Dodge Polara|Polara]] available.<ref>{{cite book|title=Standard Catalog of American Cars 1946-1975|publisher=krause publications|isbn=0-87341-027-0|editor=Gunnell, John A.}}</ref> In 1965, full sized Dodges got bigger on the new C Body with a {{convert|121|in|mm|0|abbr=on}} wheelbase, and the 330 and 440 were both replaced by the new, bigger Polara.  The [[Dodge Custom 880|880]] now took the Polara's former place in the lineup.

The '''Dodge 330 Max Wedge''' was a 330 2 door sedan powered by the 426 Max Wedge with dual 4 Barrel Carburetors and {{Convert|425|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}}.  It was available in both years, mostly ordered as a super stocker for the race tracks.  Civilian versions are rare today.

