===2009 model year===
For 2009, standard Stow 'n Go seats were added that folded flat into the rear area floor to create more cargo room, while the Swivel 'n Go seats turned 180 degrees to face the third row. The available SXT trim now included new technology options. New for 2009 was an optional "sport" suspension system as well as a blind spot warning system and "Cross Path Detection" with sensors to warn of cars or other obstacles when backing out of a parking space.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jackson |first1=Bill |title=2009 Dodge Grand Caravan Specs, Price, MPG, & Reviews |url= https://www.cars.com/research/dodge-grand_caravan-2009/ |website=cars.com |accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>

===2010 model year===
The Chrysler minivans became the only domestic brand minivans as GM and Ford replaced their slow-selling models with three-row crossover SUVs.<ref>{{cite web |title=2010 Dodge Grand Caravan Pricing, Reviews & Ratings |url= https://www.kbb.com/dodge/grand-caravan-passenger/2010/ |publisher=Kelly Blue Book |accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>

Changes for the 2010 Dodge Grand Caravans included new active head restraints for the driver and front passenger on all models, three-zone manual climate controls for the Grand Caravan SE, and a new 3.16 final drive ratio for models equipped with the 4.0-liter engine.

===2011 model year===
[[File:2011 Dodge Grand Caravan -- 06-24-2011.jpg|thumb|Post-facelift 2011 Dodge Grand Caravan]]

The Grand Caravan underwent a mid-cycle refresh for the 2011 model year, which included major changes in both styling and functionality. The suspension was heavily re-tuned, with both Dodge and Chrysler minivans gaining a larger front sway bar and new rear sway bar, increased rear roll center height, adjusted spring rates, a new steering gear, a revised front static camber setting, and lowered ride height. This improved handling.

All three of the former engine choices were replaced by the new [[Chrysler Pentastar engine|Pentastar]] 3.6-liter V6 with six-speed automatic transmission, now the sole powertrain choice for all models. Interior trim was restyled on both vans, in addition to major exterior revisions highlighted by the new "double-crosshair" grille on the Grand Caravan.

Other changes included extra sound insulation, acoustic glass, new seats, softer-touch surfaces, new [[LED]] ambient lighting and center console, and halogen projector headlamps with LED accents. The Chrysler models were adjusted so that instead of competing against equivalent Dodge trim levels, they were above Dodge in trim and features.<ref name="allpar-2011">{{cite web|url=http://www.allpar.com/model/m/11-minivans.html|title=2011 Chrysler Town & Country and 2011 Dodge Caravan Minivans|publisher=Allpar|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref>

===2012 model year===
For 2012, a new, basic style trim called "AVP" was introduced, while some features previously unavailable for "SE" (like touch navigation panel) become available as options (The "SE" now also received a floor console, similar to the one available for "SXT"). The same year, the front logo design was changed gaining the two slanted rectangles in red to match the rest of the Dodge lineup. For 2013, the American Value Package "AVP" trim [[List price|manufacturer's suggested retail price]] (MSRP) was reduced by $1,000 from the year before.

===2013 model year===
The grand Caravan added a class-exclusive feature with optional Blu-Ray DVD player while the base "AVP" model was described by [[Autotrader.com]] editors as having a "shockingly low MSRP" giving buyers "incredible utility" in their vehicle.<ref>{{cite web |title=2013 Dodge Grand Caravan Reviews and Model Information |url= https://www.autotrader.com/dodge/grand-caravan/2013 |publisher=Auto Trader |accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>

===2014 model year===
[[File:'14 Dodge Grand Caravan (MIAS '14).jpg|thumb|2014 Dodge Grand Caravan 30th Anniversary Edition on display at the [[Montreal Auto Show]], 22 January 2014]]

For the 2014 model year, three new packages are introduced: American Value Package (US; Canada Value Package in Canada), Blacktop package (US only) and the 30th Anniversary Edition. They are all different sets of the SE and SXT trims, and include new luxury features for basically the same price. The Grand Caravan AVP also gained easy-clean floor mats that came with the optional second-row Stow'n Go seats (standard on SE, SXT and R/T).

The "Blacktop package", based on SE and SXT, came equipped with 17-inch polished aluminum wheels with gloss black pockets, a gloss black grille, black headlamp bezels, an all-black interior including headliner, door panels and console, unique black cloth seats and door trim panels with silver accent stitching, a leather-wrapped steering wheel with silver accent stitching and a leather shift knob, choice of 6 body colors (Granite Crystal, Billet Silver, Brilliant Black, Maximum Steel, Redline Red, Bright White). SXT models also include fog lamps.

The "SE 30th Anniversary Edition", based on the SE trim, came equipped with 17-inch satin carbon aluminum wheels, body-color heated exterior mirrors, 30th Anniversary badging on the front fenders, silver accent stitching and piano black accents throughout, black cloth seats, a black leather-wrapped steering wheel, black leather-wrapped shift knob, black headliner and overhead console, bright heating and air conditioning trim bezels, power second- and third-row windows, and 30th Anniversary logo on the key fob

The "SXT 30th Anniversary Edition", based on the SXT trim, was packaged with 17-inch polished aluminum wheels with satin carbon pockets, bright chrome roof rack, bright window trim moldings, fog lamps, automatic headlamps and special 30th Anniversary badging, Black Torino leatherette seats with premium suede inserts and silver accent stitching, power 10-way driver's seat, piano black accent trim bezels, and bright chrome accents throughout.

Both 30th Anniversary Editions included an available special body color, Granite Crystal Pearl Coat, a customized gauge cluster with 30th Anniversary badging, as well as the UConnect Handsfree Group ([[SiriusXM]] Satellite Radio with a one-year subscription, [[Bluetooth]] streaming audio and voice command and an auto-dimming rear view mirror). The vehicles arrived at dealerships at Q3 2013.<ref>{{cite press release|url= http://media.chrysler.com/newsrelease.do?id=14744&mid=5 |title=2014 Dodge Grand Caravan Celebrates Its 30th Birthday With Even More Desirable Content and Value |publisher=Chrysler LLC |accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcarfans.com/113090462367/dodge-grand-caravan-and-chrysler-town--country-receive |title=Dodge Grand Caravan and Chrysler Town & Country receive 30th Anniversary Editions |publisher=Worldcarfans.com |date=September 3, 2013 |accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://blog.caranddriver.com/chrysler-group-celebrates-30-years-of-minivans-with-30th-anniversary-edition-grand-caravan-and-town-country/ |first=Ron |last=Sessions |title=Chrysler Group Celebrates 30 Years of Minivans with 30th Anniversary Edition Grand Caravan and Town & Country |publisher=Blog.caranddriver.com |date=September 1, 2013 |accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref>

Also new for the 2014 model year, the Grand Caravan R/T gained standard auto headlamps with black bezels and the Security Group featuring remote start and security alarm.

===2015 model year===
The Grand Caravan was not changed for the 2015 model year except for content features added to SE Plus and SXT Plus trims. The SE Plus package included black leather upholstery, power windows for the second row seats, and Chrysler's Uconnect voice command with Bluetooth sound system.

===2016 model year===
The new Chrysler Pacifica was unveiled on January 11, 2016, and getting all the attention, but the Dodge Grand Caravan continued to be marketed as a budget minivan alternative.<ref>{{cite web |title=2016 Dodge Grand Caravan: New Car Review |url= https://www.autotrader.com/car-reviews/2016-dodge-grand-caravan-new-car-review-254280 |website=autotrader.com |accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>

===2017 model year===
A small 2017 model year update yields SE, SE Plus, SXT, and GT models. The 6.5-inch Touchscreen (Radio 430 and 430 NAV) became standard equipment. (Navigation is standard on GT and optional on SXT.)<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.dodge.com/2017/grand-caravan/technology/index.html |title=2017 Dodge Grand Caravan Technology}}</ref>

FCA unveiled the [[Chrysler Pacifica (RU)|Chrysler Pacifica]], a new crossover minivan for the 2017 model year, at the 2016 [[North American International Auto Show]]. The Pacifica replaced the Chrysler Town & Country, but it was originally stated that the 2016 model of the Dodge Caravan would be produced for one more model year as a lower-cost alternative to the Pacifica, before being discontinued.<ref>{{cite news |url =http://www.freep.com/story/money/cars/chrysler/2015/12/05/2017-chrysler-minivan-coming-dodge-not-leaving-yet/76745544/ |title=2017 Chrysler minivan coming; Dodge not leaving yet |last=Priddle |first=Alisa |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |date=December 5, 2015 |accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=2017 Chrysler Pacifica: All-new ‘modern family’ minivan|url= http://www.detroitnews.com/story/business/autos/detroit-auto-show/2016/01/11/chrysler-pacifica-new-minivan-todays-modern-family/78613046/ |date=11 January 2016 |newspaper=The Detroit News |first=Michael |last=Wayland |accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dodge plans to produce '17 minivan |first=Larry P. |last=Vellequette |work=Automotive News |date=June 22, 2015 |url= http://www.autonews.com/article/20150622/OEM04/306229983/dodge-plans-to-produce-17-minivan |accessdate=March 26, 2016}}</ref><ref name="autonews-notdiscontinuedyet">{{cite web|url= http://www.autonews.com/article/20170116/OEM03/301169998/as-pacifica-ramps-up-grand-caravan-lives-on |title=As Pacifica ramps up, Grand Caravan lives on |work=Automotive News |first=Larry P. |last=Vellequette |date=January 16, 2017 |accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref> In January 2017, FCA CEO [[Sergio Marchionne]] stated that it was not clear if the Caravan would be discontinued, and that they would have to look into offering "some level of affordable access to the Pacifica at the lower end to try and replace the outgoing models" (this would eventually come in the form of the [[Chrysler Voyager#Sixth generation (2020–present)|sixth-generation Voyager]], although it is being produced alongside the Caravan). Despite the introduction of the higher-cost Pacifica model, sales of the Caravan increased by 26% in 2016.<ref name="autonews-notdiscontinuedyet"/> A substantial number of Caravans are sold to low-margin rental fleets.<ref name=Guilford22oct18>{{cite web |last=Guilford |first=Dave |title=In with the new (but keep the old) |url= https://www.autonews.com/article/20181022/OEM01/181029964/in-with-the-new-but-keep-the-old |date=22 October 2018 |accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref> The vehicle continues to be positioned for price-conscious customers and it draws traffic to dealerships when the vehicle is aggressively priced.<ref name=Guilford22oct18/> Additionally, FCA provided various rebates and incentives to assist purchases of the Grand Caravan and other models by customers with [[credit score]]s of less than 620.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sales flatten; Nissan’s big rental bet |url= https://www.kbb.com/car-news/this-week-in-car-buying-sales-flatten-nissans-big-rental-bet/2100004250/ |website=Kelley Blue Book |accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref>

According to a report by an automotive journalist, this strategy helps the Chrysler Pacifica hold its value better while also having a more affordable minivan available.<ref name="Hughes-2017"/> Over 60% of the Dodge Caravan's sales goes to fleet sales and the vehicle was the second best selling vehicle for rental fleet sales.<ref name="Hughes-2017">{{cite web |last=Hughes |first=Justin |title=Dodge Grand Caravan Continues Through 2019, But Delayed for U.S. |url= https://www.thedrive.com/sheetmetal/11815/utils/Message |website=The Drive |date=23 June 2017 |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Colias |first=Mike |title=Nissan Makes Unconventional Bet on Rental-Car Market to Boost U.S. Sales |url= https://www.wsj.com/articles/nissan-makes-unconventional-bet-on-rental-car-market-to-boost-u-s-sales-1514376000 |accessdate=14 November 2019 |work=WSJ}}</ref>

===2018 model year===
Production of Grand Caravans was temporarily suspended from September to November 2017 with the assembly of the 2018 model year versions starting in December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.donlen.com/buildstart-chrysler.html |title=Chrysler Cars (Build Out Final Order Start Up Dates) |date=May 12, 2017 |work=Donlen |accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.automotive-fleet.com/channel/vehicle-research/news/story/2017/02/fca-sets-2018-my-order-dates.aspx |title=FCA Sets 2018-MY Order Dates |date=February 28, 2017 |work=Automotive Fleet |accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref> The production line required changes to install airbags that meet U.S. Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard 226 calling for larger and more robust side-impact air curtains, as well as for them to deploy in the event of either a side-on collision or a rollover.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Layson |first=Greg |title=FCA to halt minivan output 5 weeks over U.S. airbag law |journal=Automotive News |date=14 September 2017 |url= http://www.autonews.com/article/20170914/COPY01/309149932/fca-to-halt-minivan-output-5-weeks-over-u.s.-airbag-law |accessdate=11 November 2017}}</ref>

Standard on all 2018 models are advanced multistage driver and front-passenger airbags that include low-risk deployment, a driver's-side inflatable knee blocker, front seat-mounted side airbags, and side-curtains for outboard passengers in all three rows.<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Dodge /// Durango /// Journey /// Grand Caravan |url= https://www.dodge.com/content/dam/fca-brands/na/dodge/en_us/global/pdf/brochure/18MY-Dodge-People-Mover-eBrochure-FINAL.pdf |website=dodge.com |accessdate=15 January 2018}}</ref>

For 2018, the Grand Caravan was Dodge's best-selling vehicle while the sales of foreign-branded minivans fared worse than the Dodge in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last=Willems |first=Steph |title=As Plant Preps for Downtime, America’s Grand Caravan Love Appears Unshakeable |url= https://www.thetruthaboutcars.com/2018/12/as-plant-preps-for-downtime-americas-grand-caravan-love-appears-unshakeable/ |publisher=The Truth About Cars |date=13 December 2018 |accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref>

===2019 model year===
The 2019 model year marked the 35th anniversary of the Chrysler minivans.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Minivans Celebrate 35th Anniversary with Special Edition Models |url= https://www.fcagroup.com/en-US/media_center/insights/Pages/minivans_special_edition.aspx |website=FCA Group |date=11 February 2019 |accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref> A commemorative trim option was available on the SE and SXT models that included a bright grille, 17-inch "tech silver" aluminum wheels, a 35th Anniversary fender badge as well as "piano black" console and instrument panel accents and front floor mats with 35th Anniversary embroidered logo.<ref name="2019FactSheet">{{cite web |title=2019 Dodge Grand Caravan Fact Sheet |url= https://media.fcanorthamerica.com/newsrelease.do?id=20108&mid= |publisher=Fiat Chrysler Automobiles US |date=1 September 2018 |accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref> A "Blacktop Package" featuring a black grille, headlamp bezels as well as an all-black interior was optional on SE and SXT 35th anniversary edition models.<ref name="2019FactSheet"/>

The minivan market segment decreased in general. Sales of the Grand Caravan models in Canada declined by 9% during the first quarter of 2019, but it was still number 10 among the best-selling vehicles for that period in Canada.<ref name="Driving11apr19">{{cite web |url= https://driving.ca/toyota/corolla/features/feature-story/canadas-10-best-selling-vehicles-in-2019s-first-quarter |title=Canada's 10 best-selling vehicles in the first quarter of 2019 |publisher=Driving Canada |first=Timothy |last=Cain |date=11 April 2019 |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref> Most sales went to the rental and on fleet customers.<ref name="Driving11apr19"/> The vehicle has not received major changes, but continues to be produced because "Dodge sold more than 125,000 Grand Caravans last year [2018], while Honda only sold 100,000 of its Odyssey minivans during the same year [2018]."<ref>{{cite web |title=2019 Dodge Grand Caravan Review |url= https://www.autotrader.com/car-reviews/2019-dodge-grand-caravan-review-281474979935181 |website=autotrader.com |accessdate=12 November 2019}}</ref>

The third shift at Windsor minivan plant ended in October 2019 due to sluggish sales, eliminating 1,500 direct jobs.<ref>{{cite web |last=Irwin |first=John |title=FCA extends Windsor minivan plant's third shift by 3 weeks for fleet order |url=https://canada.autonews.com/automakers/fca-extends-windsor-minivan-plants-third-shift-3-weeks-fleet-order |website=Automotive News Canada |accessdate=11 July 2019 |date=26 June 2019}}</ref>

===2020 model year===
Three models are available: SE, SE Plus, and SXT. The Grand Caravan SE Plus model now includes standard second-row Super Stow 'n Go bucket seats, power eight-way driver seat, and an all-black interior with cranberry wine accent stitching on the seats.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Dodge Grand Caravan Fact Sheet |url= https://media.fcanorthamerica.com/newsrelease.do?id=21106&fIId=20878&mid=257 |publisher=Fiat Chrysler Automobiles US |date=1 September 2019|accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref> The optional "Blacktop Package" continues for the SE Plus and SXT models.

The Canadian market includes six models starting from an entry-level version and then increasing the standard equipment on each: CVP, SXT, SXT Premium Plus, Crew, Crew Plus, and the GT that includes many convenience features as well as a performance suspension system and a monochromatic exterior.<ref>{{cite web |title=FCA Canada: 2020 Dodge Grand Caravan Fact Sheet |url=https://media.fcanorthamerica.com/newsrelease.do?id=21163&mid= |publisher=FCA Canada |date=1 September 2019 |accessdate=24 October 2019}}</ref> The "Blacktop Package" trim option is available on SXT models. 

In May 2020, the Grand Caravan will end production, with the [[Chrysler Voyager]] filling its place as FCA's budget minivan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dodge Grand Caravan Production Coming to an End|publisher=Car and Driver|first=Colin|last=Beresford|date=February 28, 2020|url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/a31156055/dodge-grand-caravan-end-production/|accessdate=February 28, 2020}}</ref>

