The new Ramcharger was produced in Mexico from 1998 for the 1999 model year, based on the same platform as the [[Dodge Ram]] pickup and sharing most of its componentry with the Ram as well.<ref name=SS03>{{cite book | ref = SS03 | title = Katalog Samochody Świata 2003 | trans-title = World Car Catalogue 2003 | editor-first = Eligiusz | editor-last = Mazur | publisher = Print Shops Prego - Polska Sp. z o.o. | location = Warsaw, Poland | page = 217 | date = 2002 | issn = 1234-8198 }}</ref> It had also shared some of its parts and components with the third generation Chrysler minivans (Chrysler Town & Country, Dodge Caravan/Plymouth Voyager) as well. It was only sold in Mexico where the previous generation Ramcharger had been successful. It was available in the ST, SLT, SLT Plus and Sport trim levels. Powered by the {{convert|318|CID|L|1|abbr=on}} or {{convert|360|CID|L|1|abbr=on}} Magnum V8 engines and offered only in rear-wheel drive versions, it was discontinued after the 2001 model year.

One of the features of this generation was a small third row folding seat in the cargo area that faced sideways, making it less practical for long trips. The rear of the vehicle had looked very similar to the 1996-2000 model Chrysler minivans.

{{citation needed span|text=This version of the Ramcharger was not sold in the US for numerous reasons:|date=June 2019}} 
*{{citation needed span|text=Two-door SUV sales had been declining (GM soon ended production of its two-door Tahoe and Yukon, and Ford replaced the long-running two-door only [[Ford Bronco]] around the same time with the four-door only [[Ford Expedition]]).|date=June 2019}}
*{{citation needed span|text=[[DaimlerChrysler]] had just launched two successful mid-sized SUVs ([[Jeep Grand Cherokee]] and [[Dodge Durango]]), which would have been showroom-competitors with a third generation Ramcharger.|date=June 2019}} 
*{{citation needed span|text=Finally, this large SUV would have negatively affected the company's [[Corporate Average Fuel Economy]] for a very small projected sales return.|date=June 2019}}

