[[File:Davie, Florida (3313349071).jpg|thumbnail|left|Rear view (Charger R/T)]]
Both the SXT and R/T models were available in rear and all-wheel drive drive trains starting in 2007. The [[All-wheel drive|AWD]] system is derived from the [[Mercedes-Benz]] [[4Matic]] technology. The AWD system is engaged all the time, routing approximately 60% of the power to the rear wheels and 40% of the power to the front wheels. The 2009 Charger AWD utilized the [[BorgWarner#TorqTransfer Systems|Torque-on-Demand]] system manufactured by [[BorgWarner]] which disconnects the front axles until extra traction is needed. This results in a slight boost in fuel economy while retaining the same maximum power split to the front wheels.

After three years of production, an update for 2009 models was made. This included moving the rear decklid's "CHARGER" badge from the left to the right, making way for "DODGE" at the left. Tail lamps were also revised. 2008 models had seen minor revisions to the interior (a new center console and switchgear changes).

===Engines===
[[File:5 7hemi.jpg|thumb|left|alt=5.7L Hemi|5.7 L Hemi]]
[[File:6 1hemi.jpg|thumb|left|alt=6.1L Hemi|6.1 L Hemi]]

The Charger ''SE'' and ''SXT'' are equipped with [[Chrysler 3.3 engine#3.5|Chrysler's 3.5 L V6]], rated at {{convert|250|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|250|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque. In Canada, the base model Charger has a 2.7 L V6, which is rated at {{convert|178|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|190|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque. In 2006, the 2.7 L V6 was also available in the U.S. for fleet sales only. For 2007, the SE package could be had with the 2.7 L engine for all buyers. The Canadian SXT model included the 3.5 L V6.

The ''R/T'' version uses the [[Chrysler Hemi engine#5.7|5.7 L Hemi V8 engine]]. From 2006 to 2008, this engine was rated at {{convert|340|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|390|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque. For 2009, Variable Camshaft Timing was added, raising power output levels to {{convert|368|hp|kW|abbr=on}} and {{convert|395|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque respectively.

The ''SRT8'' model comes with the [[Chrysler Hemi engine#6.1|{{convert|370|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|order=flip}} Hemi V8]], which is rated at {{convert|425|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|420|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://runbidsell.com/resources/2010-dodge-charger-srt8/ |title=2010 Dodge Charger SRT8 Technical Specs|}}</ref>

