===Daytona R/T===
[[File:Dodge Charger Daytona RT (20878152454).jpg|thumbnail|right|Dodge Charger Daytona R/T]]

The 2006 '''Charger Daytona R/T''' debuted at the [[Chicago Auto Show]]. It featured a high output {{convert|350|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} version of the {{convert|345|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|order=flip}} Hemi as well as an updated suspension and tires. Visual additions included a special front fascia with a chin spoiler and a black rear spoiler. In a retro touch, the Daytona R/T featured black "Hemi" decals on the hood and rear fender and retro high impact colors.  

The 2006 Dodge Charger R/T Daytona Limited colors were “GO MAN.GO!” (orange with black decals & spoiler (punctuation in the name is correct, as displayed on dash)), "TOP BANANA” (Yellow with black decals & spoiler), "TOR.RED” (red with black decals & spoiler (punctuation in the name is correct, as displayed on dash)). Each color was production limited and badged under the far right vent.  The U.S. production release was limited to 4,000 cars each for orange and yellow, 2,000 for the red, and badged with a production number under the far right dash vent.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.roadandtrack.com/new-cars/first-drives/reviews/a11007/2006-dodge-charger-daytona-rt/|title=2006 Dodge Charger Daytona R/T|date=2012-11-06|first=Matt|last=Delorenzo|magazine=[[Road & Track]]|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref>

In 2007, larger 20-inch chrome-clad wheels were introduced along with two new colors, Sub Lime Green and Plum Crazy Purple.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.autos.ca/car-test-drives/test-drive-2007-dodge-charger-daytona-rt/|title=Test Drive: 2007 Dodge Charger Daytona R/T|date=2007-08-14|first=Peter|last=Bleakney|publisher=Autos.ca|accessdate=2019-10-17}}</ref> In 2008, a revised stripe package was adopted. In 2009, horsepower was increased to {{convert|372|hp|kW|0|abbr=on}} by the addition of Variable Camshaft Timing.

{{Clear}}

===SRT-8===
<!-- Dodge Super bee links to this section -->
{{See also|Street and Racing Technology}}
An '''SRT8''' version of the Charger debuted at the 2005 [[New York International Auto Show]]. Powered by a {{convert|425|hp|PS kW|0|abbr=on}} version of the ''[[Chrysler Hemi engine#6.1|{{convert|370|cuin|L|1|abbr=on|order=flip}} Hemi]]'', it also featured upgraded [[Brembo]] brakes, and interior and exterior updates. The engine produces {{convert|420|lbft|Nm|0|abbr=on}} of torque at 4,800 rpm. The 425 [[Horsepower#SAE net power|SAE net horsepower]] of the modern 6.1 L Hemi makes it even more powerful than the [[Chrysler Hemi engine]]s of the [[muscle car]] era, the biggest of which was rated at 425 [[Horsepower#SAE gross power|SAE gross horsepower]]. This made the 6.1 L Hemi engine the most powerful [[V8 engine]] that [[Chrysler]] had put in a production vehicle up to that point. The SRT8 can accelerate from {{convert|0-60|mph|km/h|abbr=on}} in 4.8 seconds (5.0 average).<ref name="caranddriver.com">Page 11: [http://www.caranddriver.com/features/the-quickest-sedans-of-2008-30000-to-40000-2008-dodge-charger-srt8-page-11 The Quickest Sedans of 2008: $30,000 to $40,000 - Car Comparison - Feature Article - Page 11], accessdate: 20. tammikuuta 2016</ref>
