{{Single source|date=February 2019}}

The '''Dodge Crusader''' is an automobile built by [[Dodge|Dodge Canada]]. Initially introduced in 1951, the original Crusader was a [[badge engineering|rebadged]] [[Plymouth Cambridge]] fitted with a long-block {{convert|218|cuin|cc|0|abbr=on}} [[straight-six engine|flathead-six engine]].<ref name="allpar">{{cite web |url=http://www.allpar.com/world/canada.html |title=Chrysler Canada, 1924 to 2014 |publisher=Allpar.com |accessdate=7 July 2015}}</ref> For 1954, the Crusader nameplate was switched to a rebadged version of the [[Plymouth Plaza]], and it remained in production until 1958.<ref name="allpar"/>

